  "misconception": {
    "claim": "A falling object keeps accelerating until it lands.",
    "refuted_by": "With air resistance the acceleration decays toward zero as drag grows to cancel gravity, so the object approaches a constant terminal velocity. On the a-t graph, $a \\to 0$ — the opposite of constant-gravity free fall, where $a$ stays at $-10$ the whole way."
  },
